Mobile service provider Infinix Zero 5 flagship is seemingly the must have smartphone in the market after its recent launch. Launched on November 14th, the Zero 5 Pro is a complete upgrade compared to the Zero 4 and Zero 4 Plus with special features like an Octa Core Helio P25 processor from Mediatek giving it a fluid performance. With a 5.98-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 1080 pixels by 1920 pixels, a 12-megapixel primary camera on the rear and a 16-megapixel front shooter for selfies making it the company’s flagship going into 2018 and is a camera-centric device just like all the devices under the ‘Zero’ family.